The Commonwealth Office of Technology shall consist of the following five (5) offices, each headed by an executive director and organized into divisions headed by a division director:
Office of Enterprise Technology, consisting of the:
Division of IT Governance; and
Division of Enterprise Architecture;
Office of Infrastructure Services, consisting of the:
Division of Technical Services;
Division of Communications;
Division of IT Operations; and
Division of Field Services;
Office of Application Development, consisting of the:
Division of Revenue Application Development;
Division of Agency Application Development;
Division of Development Support Services;
Division of Geographic Information Systems; and
Division of Data Management Services;
Office of Chief Information Security Officer. The office shall ensure the efficiency and effectiveness of information technology security functions and responsibilities; and
Office of Information Technology Service Management.
